## AutoShutdown thru Home Assistant

/usr/local/bin/request_rasp4b_powercut.sh
```
#!/bin/bash
HA_URL="http://<ip_home_assistant>:8123"
TOKEN="abcdefghijklmonpqrst"
SCRIPT_ENTITY="script.rasp4b_poweroff"
curl -s -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"entity_id\":\"$SCRIPT_ENTITY\"}" \
  "$HA_URL/api/services/script/turn_on" >/dev/null 2>&1
```
Setting restricted access in order to protect the Token
```
chmod 500 /usr/local/bin/request_rasp4b_powercut.sh
```
Lets have a look at /etc/systemd/system/MyPowerCut.service
```
[Unit]
Description=Request delayed Raspberry power cut via Home Assistant
DefaultDependencies=no
Before=poweroff.target halt.target
Wants=network-online.target
After=network-online.target

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/request_rasp4b_powercut.sh
TimeoutStartSec=15

[Install]
WantedBy=poweroff.target halt.target
```
